---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="The Quick Guide to Zero-Party Data for E-Commerce - parcelLab"
  description="Learn what zero-party data is, why it matters for e-commerce, and how to collect it effectively to build better customer relationships."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Post-Purchase</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">The Quick Guide to Zero-Party Data for E-Commerce</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2022-11-09">November 9, 2022</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>6 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          In recent years, marketers have relied heavily on third-party data -- information collected about potential customers and sold to advertisers for targeting purposes. But a new approach is emerging that's more cost-effective, more direct, and more tied to actual customer preferences: zero-party data.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">What Is Zero-Party Data?</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The industry has utilized <strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">second-party data</strong> (collected by one company and shared with another) and <strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">first-party data</strong> (conclusions drawn from customers' behavior and brand interactions). <strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Zero-party data</strong> represents the next evolution: information customers actively choose to share with brands intentionally.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Why It Matters Right Now</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Legislative Changes</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              The 2018 GDPR and CCPA established restrictions on data collection and tracking. Subsequently, over 160 consumer privacy bills were introduced across 38 U.S. states. Tech companies have responded -- Apple blocks third-party cookies in Safari, with Google Chrome planning similar changes.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Consumer Demand</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              79% of Americans worry about how companies use their data, with increasing adoption of ad blockers and cookie deletion practices.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Data Quality Issues</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              E-commerce retailers recognize that third-party data can be unreliable. 49% of consumers say they're frustrated by irrelevant content and offers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Zero-Party Data and E-Commerce</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Zero-party data offers e-commerce businesses improved customer understanding and significant potential for increased satisfaction, repeat purchases, and lifetime value. Successful implementation requires strategic adjustments:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Start small:</strong> Request only essential information initially, building profiles gradually to avoid overwhelming customers.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Stay focused:</strong> Collect data exclusively for personalization and targeted rewards.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Keep communicating:</strong> Zero-party data collection extends throughout the post-purchase journey, using every touchpoint to deepen customer understanding.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Be transparent:</strong> Clearly explain what data you need, why it's collected, and how it will be protected.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Offer instant rewards:</strong> Provide short-term incentives like discounts, sweepstakes, or early product access to demonstrate appreciation.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          When executed correctly, zero-party data creates a positive feedback loop: improved communication leads to deeper customer insights, enabling more relevant messaging that strengthens the relationship further.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
